# The hashes below are placeholders pinned in feature-001 scaffolding. They are
# replaced with real SHA-256 values by the recording job in Phase 3 US1 (T022) when
# the weights are actually downloaded. The CI guard (scripts/check_slm_pinning.py,
# T126) refuses to start the SLM container until every artifact's actual SHA matches.
#
# Real artifact list (from the Hugging Face snapshot at the pinned revision):
#   model-00001-of-00004.safetensors
#   model-00002-of-00004.safetensors
#   model-00003-of-00004.safetensors
#   model-00004-of-00004.safetensors
#   model.safetensors.index.json
#   config.json
#   generation_config.json
#   tokenizer.json
#   tokenizer_config.json
#   vocab.json
#   merges.txt
#
# CPU-fallback profile additionally records:
#   qwen2.5-7b-instruct-q4_k_m.gguf
#
# Until the recording job runs, these entries are intentionally absent. The build
# fails closed: scripts/verify_slm_manifest.py treats an empty manifest as a manifest
# error, not a successful no-op.
